<p><b>Cecil Antonio "Tony" Richardson</b> (5 June 1928 – 14 November 1991) was an English theatre and film director and producer. He was married to <a href="Vanessa_Redgrave" title="Vanessa Redgrave">Vanessa Redgrave</a> from 1962 until 1969, with whom he had his two daughters: <a href="Natasha_Richardson" title="Natasha Richardson">Natasha</a> and <a href="Joely_Richardson" title="Joely Richardson">Joely Richardson</a>. He had a five-decade film career. In 1964 he won the Academy Award for Best Director for the film <i><a href="Tom_Jones_(film)" title="Tom Jones (film)">Tom Jones</a></i>. He died from AIDS at 63 in 1991.</p>
